Lo Mein (sauce from Three Many Cooks)
http://www.brannyboilsover.com/2013/01/17/veggie-lo-mein/

2 cups snow peas, washed and trimmed
1 red bell pepper, washed and diced
3 cloves garlic, crushed
3 cups mung bean sprouts
2 scallions, sliced
8 ounces lo mein noodles
1/4 cup vegetable broth
1/4 cup soy sauce
1 Tablespoon sesame oil
1 Tablespoon brown sugar
2 teaspoons rice vinegar

Bring a large pot of water to boil and cook lo mein noodles as directed.

Meanwhile, heat a 12" skillet over high heat. Coat with cooking spray and
when hot, add bell pepper. Stir fry 3-4 minutes until they begin to blacken.
Reduce heat to medium and add garlic and snowpeas. Cook until snowpeas are
bright green.

Combine broth, soy sauce, oil, and brown sugar in a small bowl. When
vegetables are done cooking, add sauce to skillet and coat vegetables.

In a large bowl combine scallions, bean sprouts, cooked lo mein noodles, and
stir fried vegetables and sauce.
